Instructions

In this lab, youll be working with the tents dataset included in this folder. You may use any of the packages that weve covered in class so far. Youll need to start by reading in the data with read_csv from readr of course.

Histograms and Densities

  1. Create a histogram of tent prices. Youll need the geom_histogram() geometry.

ggplot(mpg,aes(class)) +geom_bar

  1. Adjust the binwidth to 50 with the binwidth argument of geom_histogram().

  2. Add a density estimate layer to your plot in number 2 using geom_density(). Youll need map ..density.. to the y aesthetic for this to work. #histogram: count, not density.

  3. Generate a density price, colored by bestuse. Youll probably want a fixed alpha value of 0.5.

Boxplots

  1. Generate a bar chart of with the counts of brands. geom_bar.

  2. Modify the code from number 1 to add color for the brands.

  3. Create a bar chart of brand colored by bestuse.

Scatter Plots

  1. Create a scatter plot of height vs. weight. Color and shape the points by bestuse.

  2. Add a line of best fit under the points using geom_smooth. Use method = "lm" to produce a line rather than a polynomial. Change se to FALSE to remove the confidence regions. Lastly, change the color of the line to grey75.

Faceting

Create a scatter plots of weight vs price. Facet wrap by capacity. Color by brand.

In conjunction with wrangling

Try to reproduce the graph below, titles and all. Youll need to wrangle the data some. The size of the points is 1.5, and the color of the line-of-best-fit is grey75.
